<item>
  <title>Courbes IDF avec R</title>
  <dc:creator>NEBIE Gaston Cyrille</dc:creator>
  <link>https://ngastoncyrille.github.io/blog/posts/idf-curves-r/index.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 



<div class="row g-2 mb-4">
<div class="col-auto">
<span class="tag tag-r">R</span>
</div>
<div class="col-auto">
<span class="tag tag-water">Hydrologie</span>
</div>
<div class="col-auto">
<span class="tag tag-water">IDF</span>
</div>
<div class="col-auto">
<span class="tag tag-risk">Analyse fréquentielle</span>
</div>
</div>
<p><em>Aussi disponible sur <a href="https://rpubs.com/nebiegc" target="_blank">RPubs — P_f bk2020_007 &amp; 008</a></em></p>
<hr>
<section id="introduction" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="introduction">Introduction</h2>
<p>Les courbes <strong>Intensité-Durée-Fréquence (IDF)</strong> sont des outils fondamentaux en hydrologie pour la conception des ouvrages hydrauliques (dimensionnement de caniveaux, bassins de rétention, ponts…). Elles permettent de lier :</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Intensité</strong> (mm/h) : le débit moyen de la pluie sur une durée donnée</li>
<li><strong>Durée</strong> (min, h) : le temps de la pluie observée<br>
</li>
<li><strong>Fréquence</strong> (ou période de retour, en années)</li>
</ul>
<p>Dans ce tutoriel, nous allons construire des courbes IDF à partir de données pluviographiques réelles en utilisant uniquement le langage <strong>R</strong>.</p>
<hr>
</section>
<section id="données-nécessaires" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="données-nécessaires">Données nécessaires</h2>
<p>Les données requises sont des <strong>relevés pluviographiques</strong> à pas de temps fin (5 min, 10 min, 15 min, 30 min, 1h) sur une longue série (≥ 20 ans idéalement).</p>
<div class="cell">
<details>
<summary>Code</summary>
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb1" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb1-1"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># Structure attendue des données</span></span>
<span id="cb1-2"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># station : identifiant de la station</span></span>
<span id="cb1-3"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># date    : date de l'événement</span></span>
<span id="cb1-4"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># duree   : durée (en minutes)</span></span>
<span id="cb1-5"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># pluie   : hauteur de pluie (mm)</span></span>
<span id="cb1-6"></span>
<span id="cb1-7"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># Exemple de création d'un jeu de données simulé</span></span>
<span id="cb1-8"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">set.seed</span>(<span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">42</span>)</span>
<span id="cb1-9"></span>
<span id="cb1-10">durees <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">c</span>(<span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">5</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">10</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">15</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">30</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">60</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">120</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">360</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">720</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">1440</span>) <span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># en minutes</span></span>
<span id="cb1-11">n_annees <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">30</span></span>
<span id="cb1-12"></span>
<span id="cb1-13"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># Simuler des maximums annuels (distribution GEV)</span></span>
<span id="cb1-14"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">library</span>(evd)</span>
<span id="cb1-15">data_idf <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">expand.grid</span>(</span>
<span id="cb1-16">  <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">annee =</span> <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">1991</span><span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">:</span><span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">2020</span>,</span>
<span id="cb1-17">  <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">duree =</span> durees</span>
<span id="cb1-18">)</span>
<span id="cb1-19">data_idf<span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">$</span>pluie <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">rgev</span>(<span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">nrow</span>(data_idf), <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">loc =</span> <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">20</span>, <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">scale =</span> <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">8</span>, <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">shape =</span> <span class="fl" style="color: #AD0000;">0.1</span>)</span>
<span id="cb1-20"></span>
<span id="cb1-21"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">head</span>(data_idf, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">12</span>)</span></code></pre></div>
</details>
</div>
<hr>
</section>
<section id="ajustement-statistique" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="ajustement-statistique">Ajustement statistique</h2>
<section id="loi-de-gumbel-distribution-des-extrêmes" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="loi-de-gumbel-distribution-des-extrêmes">Loi de Gumbel (distribution des extrêmes)</h3>
<p>La loi de <strong>Gumbel (Extrême Value Type I)</strong> est couramment utilisée pour l’analyse fréquentielle des précipitations extrêmes.</p>
<div class="cell">
<details>
<summary>Code</summary>
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb2" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb2-1"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">library</span>(dplyr)</span>
<span id="cb2-2"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">library</span>(ggplot2)</span>
<span id="cb2-3"></span>
<span id="cb2-4"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># Fonction d'ajustement Gumbel par durée</span></span>
<span id="cb2-5">ajuster_gumbel <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;">function</span>(x) {</span>
<span id="cb2-6">  n <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">length</span>(x)</span>
<span id="cb2-7">  mu <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">mean</span>(x)</span>
<span id="cb2-8">  sigma <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">sd</span>(x) <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">*</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">sqrt</span>(<span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">6</span>) <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">/</span> pi</span>
<span id="cb2-9">  u <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> mu <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">-</span> <span class="fl" style="color: #AD0000;">0.5772</span> <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">*</span> sigma</span>
<span id="cb2-10">  <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">return</span>(<span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">list</span>(<span class="at" style="color: #657422;">u =</span> u, <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">sigma =</span> sigma))</span>
<span id="cb2-11">}</span>
<span id="cb2-12"></span>
<span id="cb2-13"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># Périodes de retour</span></span>
<span id="cb2-14">T_retour <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">c</span>(<span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">2</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">5</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">10</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">20</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">50</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">100</span>)</span>
<span id="cb2-15"></span>
<span id="cb2-16"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># Fonction quantile Gumbel</span></span>
<span id="cb2-17">q_gumbel <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;">function</span>(T, u, sigma) {</span>
<span id="cb2-18">  yT <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">-</span><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">log</span>(<span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">-</span><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">log</span>(<span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">1</span> <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">-</span> <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">1</span><span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">/</span>T))</span>
<span id="cb2-19">  <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">return</span>(u <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">+</span> sigma <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">*</span> yT)</span>
<span id="cb2-20">}</span>
<span id="cb2-21"></span>
<span id="cb2-22"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># Calcul des quantiles par durée et période de retour</span></span>
<span id="cb2-23">resultats <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> data_idf <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">|&gt;</span></span>
<span id="cb2-24">  <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">group_by</span>(duree) <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">|&gt;</span></span>
<span id="cb2-25">  <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">summarise</span>(<span class="at" style="color: #657422;">params =</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">list</span>(<span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">ajuster_gumbel</span>(pluie)), <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">.groups =</span> <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"drop"</span>) <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">|&gt;</span></span>
<span id="cb2-26">  <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">mutate</span>(</span>
<span id="cb2-27">    <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">u     =</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">sapply</span>(params, <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">`</span><span class="at" style="color: #657422;">[[</span><span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">`</span>, <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"u"</span>),</span>
<span id="cb2-28">    <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">sigma =</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">sapply</span>(params, <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">`</span><span class="at" style="color: #657422;">[[</span><span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">`</span>, <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"sigma"</span>)</span>
<span id="cb2-29">  )</span>
<span id="cb2-30"></span>
<span id="cb2-31"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># Calculer les intensités (mm/h) pour chaque période de retour</span></span>
<span id="cb2-32">idf_table <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> resultats <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">|&gt;</span></span>
<span id="cb2-33">  <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">select</span>(duree, u, sigma) <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">|&gt;</span></span>
<span id="cb2-34">  <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">rowwise</span>() <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">|&gt;</span></span>
<span id="cb2-35">  <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">mutate</span>(<span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">across</span>(<span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">starts_with</span>(<span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"u"</span>), <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">~</span><span class="cn" style="color: #8f5902;">NULL</span>)) <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">|&gt;</span></span>
<span id="cb2-36">  <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">bind_cols</span>(</span>
<span id="cb2-37">    <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">setNames</span>(</span>
<span id="cb2-38">      <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">lapply</span>(T_retour, <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;">function</span>(T) {</span>
<span id="cb2-39">        (<span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">q_gumbel</span>(T, resultats<span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">$</span>u, resultats<span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">$</span>sigma) <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">/</span> resultats<span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">$</span>duree) <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">*</span> <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">60</span></span>
<span id="cb2-40">      }),</span>
<span id="cb2-41">      <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">paste0</span>(<span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"T"</span>, T_retour)</span>
<span id="cb2-42">    )</span>
<span id="cb2-43">  )</span>
<span id="cb2-44"></span>
<span id="cb2-45"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">print</span>(idf_table)</span></code></pre></div>
</details>
</div>
<hr>
</section>
</section>
<section id="construction-des-courbes-idf" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="construction-des-courbes-idf">Construction des courbes IDF</h2>
<div class="cell">
<details>
<summary>Code</summary>
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb3" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb3-1"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">library</span>(tidyr)</span>
<span id="cb3-2"></span>
<span id="cb3-3"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># Mise en format long pour la visualisation</span></span>
<span id="cb3-4">idf_long <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> idf_table <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">|&gt;</span></span>
<span id="cb3-5">  <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">select</span>(duree, <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">starts_with</span>(<span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"T"</span>)) <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">|&gt;</span></span>
<span id="cb3-6">  <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">pivot_longer</span>(</span>
<span id="cb3-7">    <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">cols      =</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">starts_with</span>(<span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"T"</span>),</span>
<span id="cb3-8">    <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">names_to  =</span> <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"periode_retour"</span>,</span>
<span id="cb3-9">    <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">values_to =</span> <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"intensite"</span></span>
<span id="cb3-10">  ) <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">|&gt;</span></span>
<span id="cb3-11">  <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">mutate</span>(</span>
<span id="cb3-12">    <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">periode_retour =</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">factor</span>(</span>
<span id="cb3-13">      <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">gsub</span>(<span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"T"</span>, <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">""</span>, periode_retour),</span>
<span id="cb3-14">      <span class="at" style="color: #657422;">levels =</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">as.character</span>(T_retour)</span>
<span id="cb3-15">    )</span>
<span id="cb3-16">  )</span>
<span id="cb3-17"></span>
<span id="cb3-18"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;"># Palette de couleurs</span></span>
<span id="cb3-19">palette_idf <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;">c</span>(</span>
<span id="cb3-20">  <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"2"</span>   <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">=</span> <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"#90e0ef"</span>,</span>
<span id="cb3-21">  <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"5"</span>   <span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;">=</span> <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;">"#48cae4"</span>,</span>
